# Generate AI Quote

You are generating a bespoke client quote for PRAGMA, an AI consulting agency.

## Input
The argument is a path to a markdown file with this structure:
```
---
client_name: Acme Corp
client_email: cto@acme.com
client_company: Acme Corp
title: "AI-Powered Customer Support Automation"
currency: USD
locale: en
valid_until: "2026-06-30"
---

[Markdown body: full narrative of the engagement, problem, solution, deliverables, investment, next steps]
```

## Steps

1. **Read the input file** at the path provided as $ARGUMENTS.

2. **Extract the quote ID**: Generate a 10-character nanoid-style ID (alphanumeric, URL-safe) that will be used as both the DB id and the directory name. Example: `xK9mP2qR4s`.

3. **Generate `src/generated-quotes/Quote_[id]/QuoteContent.tsx`**:
   - A React Client Component (`"use client"` directive)
   - Props: `{ quote: Quote }` imported from `@/features/quotes/types`
   - Uses only Tailwind 4 utility classes (NO tailwind.config.ts — tokens are in globals.css as CSS variables: `pragma-bg`, `pragma-surface`, `pragma-border`, `pragma-accent`, `pragma-accent-2`, `pragma-accent-3`, `pragma-text`, `pragma-muted`, font-display: Space Grotesk)
   - Layout must be bespoke — not a copy of QuoteViewer. Design it to showcase the specific engagement.
   - Must NOT include the PRAGMA header/nav, locale switcher, PDF button, or Accept button — those are injected by AiQuoteShell.
   - Must export a named export: `export function QuoteContent({ quote }: { quote: Quote })`

4. **Generate `src/generated-quotes/Quote_[id]/QuotePDF.tsx`**:
   - Uses `@react-pdf/renderer` (Document, Page, Text, View, StyleSheet — no Canvas, no Image unless you have a URL)
   - Props: `{ quote: Quote }`
   - Named export: `export function QuotePDF({ quote }: { quote: Quote })`
   - White background, dark text — PDFs don't render CSS variables. Use hex values directly.
   - Mirror the structure of the web component but translated to PDF primitives.

5. **Update `src/generated-quotes/registry.ts`**:
   - Add the import lines for QuoteContent and QuotePDF
   - Add the entry to the `quoteRegistry` object
   - Preserve all existing entries — only append, never remove

6. **Insert the DB row** by running:
